    "speaker": "interviewee",
    "tag": "AV",
    "text": "This is my great-grandmother, Brana Schwartz, born in 1854 and died in Auschwitz in 1944, at the age of 90. This is my grandmother, [? Cilly ?] Katz, born in 1887, died in 1945, January 1945, in Varosmajor in Budapest, Hungary. She's the daughter of Brana Schwartz-Katz. This is my grandpa, Leopold Katz, [? Cilly's ?] husband, my father's father. He was born in 1878 and died in 1944. This is my grandpa, Herman Gluck, my mother's-- Irene's father. And he was born in 1887 and died in 1946 in Budapest. This is my grandmother, Maria Gluck, born Maria [? Reis ?] in 1888. And she died in 1945 in Budapest. This is my father, Armin Katz, born 1909 in Maramarossziget, died in 1983 in New York. And my mother, Irene, born Irene Gluck in 1914 in Nyirbator and is still living in the Jewish Home for the Elderly in Fairfield, Connecticut.",
