  {
    "speaker": "interviewee",
    "tag": "AV",
    "text": "This is the family passport photo from 1946. We have always wanted to come to the United States. We had a passport. We just didn't have a visa. That's my father, my mother, myself and my sister, Susan. This is a picture of me at age six, in 1946, just after the Holocaust. This is my daughter, Vivion Lynn Vertes, at the age of 25 in 1980-- 1993. And she currently lives in Los Angeles, California. This is my family-- my husband, Michael, standing behind me, my son, Roger, on my left, my daughter-in-law, Rina, on my right, and my beautiful little granddaughter, Marissa, who is only-- not quite three months old.",
